  "prompt": "Where did the name Twitter come from?",
  "response": "Twitter's name originated from the word \"tweet,\" which means a short burst of communication, like a bird's chirp. Jack Dorsey, one of the platform's founders, reportedly suggested the name during a brainstorming session with other co-founders. The name was meant to evoke the idea of short, quick messages that users could send, similar to a bird's tweet. The company was founded in 2006 and launched the social media platform in the same year.",
